{"chunk_id": "e354b199-c326-4e22-ade3-5d61b56badfc", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 221, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "vital body fluids. Water plays a key role in elimination of body wastes and regulation of body temperature. The body loses water through sweat, urine and faeces. This loss must be constantly made good with clean and potable water. A normal healthy person needs to drink about 8 glasses (2 litre) of water per day. During very hot weather and while undertaking vigorous physical activity, this requirement increases as a considerable amount of water is lost through sweat. Water should be safe and wholesome i.e., it should be free from disease-causing agents like bacteria, viruses, parasites etc., and harmful chemical substances like pesticides, industrial wastes, heavy metals, nitrates, arsenic and excess of fluoride. Fluorosis, a disease with bone deformities and dental problems, results from", "embedding": [-0.01247384212911129, 0.036176979541778564, 0.03002040460705757, 0.03737457096576691, 0.06934917718172073, -0.019491810351610184, 0.08505450189113617, 0.04839945584535599, -0.08534187078475952, 0.021862221881747246, -0.06290804594755173, -0.054887060075998306, 0.031385861337184906, 0.07969781756401062, -0.09015344828367233, -0.06956005096435547, -0.05576028302311897, -0.008552617393434048, -0.07629166543483734, 0.05772249773144722, 0.062263038009405136, -0.001996333012357354, 0.023721080273389816, -0.009775998070836067, -0.08492553234100342, 0.001599336857907474, 0.12107838690280914, -0.07303555309772491, -0.02943168208003044, 0.05904555320739746, 0.07104018330574036, 0.05679582804441452, 0.03149983286857605, -0.1651035100221634, -0.06624996662139893, 0.04499867931008339, 0.036628711968660355, -0.06883479654788971, -0.07618356496095657, -0.02277156338095665, -0.004845892079174519, -0.02684577554464340